'''Joe Louis''' was a [[horse]] owned by the [[United States Army]]. He was purchased by the Army in 1938 and named in honor of boxer [[Joe Louis]]. Joe Louis died at [[Fort Riley, Kansas]] in 1957 and was the last of three living operational cavalry mounts of the U.S. Army, the others being [[Chief (horse)|Chief]] and Gambler.<ref name="jet">{{cite news |title = Cavalry Horse, Joe Louis, Dies in Kansas |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=UbcDAAAAMBAJ |work = [[Jet (magazine)|Jet]] |date = December 19, 1957 |page = 50 |access-date = July 18, 2018 |via = [[Google News]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title = Old Soldier of the Cavalry Passes On |url = https://www.newspapers.com/clip/21965837/old_soldier_of_the_cavalry_passes_on/ |access-date = July 18, 2018 |work = [[Manhattan Mercury]] |date = December 8, 1957 |page = 9 |via = [[Newspapers.com]] }} {{free access}}</ref>

