{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}} {{Use Australian English|date=June 2014}} '''Neville Francis''' "'''Nifty'''" '''Sellwood''' (2 December 1922 − 7 November 1962) was an [[Australians|Australian]] [[jockey]] who was known for, among other victories, riding [[Delta (horse)|Delta]] and [[Toparoa]] to victory in the 1951 and 1955 [[Melbourne Cup]] races, respectively. He also rode Larkspur to victory in the 1962 Epsom Derby. <ref> Neville has also ridden Tulloch and Todman during his lifetime. [http://www.progroupracing.com.au/horse-racing-articles/jockeys/neville-sellwood Neville Sellwood]</ref> The [[Neville Sellwood Stakes]], hosted by the [[Australian Turf Club]], was named in honour of him.
Sellwood was born on 2 December 1922 in [[Hamilton, Queensland|Hamilton]], an inner-suburb of [[Brisbane]], [[Queensland]].
Sellwood died after the horse he was riding slipped and fell on the track of the [[Maisons-Laffitte Racecourse]] on 7 November 1962, aged 39, in [[Maisons-Laffitte]], [[France]].<ref>[http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/sellwood-neville-francis-11656 Sellwood, Neville Francis (1922–1962)]</ref>
In 2002, Sellwood was inducted into the [[Australian Racing Hall of Fame]].<ref>[http://www.efreebets.com.au/horse-racing/neville-sellwood-jockey Neville Sellwood biography]</ref> ==References== {{Reflist}}
